## 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History

**Freshness: High - recently verified in this session**

Phase 3 should preserve a frictionless local portfolio experience while adding an explicitly enabled shared/authenticated mode. The likely direction is server-validated bearer credentials mapped to tenant and role, with secrets supplied only through environment or Streamlit secret storage and never through URLs or browser-local persistence. Health liveness may remain public; resource APIs should be protected when authentication mode is enabled.

Tenant scope should live on top-level resources and be enforced in repositories and service entry points, not merely filtered in the UI. Existing databases should backfill a stable default tenant so Phase 2 data remains usable. Idempotency and name/version uniqueness should become tenant-local. Child access should inherit scope through scoped parent ownership and joins.

Dashboard cache identity must include the principal/tenant context so one signed-in identity cannot receive another identity's cached data. The evaluation executor may use system-level internal lookup for globally unique run IDs, but public access must never bypass tenant scope.

The cold-route fix must address the true Streamlit bootstrap/navigation cause rather than hide the overlay with CSS. Durable queue work must use database-backed, atomic lease semantics and explicit retry/recovery behavior if it is implemented. External GitHub, hosted CI, paid-provider, and production claims remain separate proof layers.

